WarningDescription
WRITE ERRORMemory card error or connection error: Reinsert the card or turn the camera off and then on again. If the message persists, contact a Fujifilm dealer. Not enough memory remaining to record additional pictures: Delete pictures or insert a memory card with more free space. ● The memory card is not formatted: Format the memory card. ● The memory card was removed while data were being recorded: Do not remove the memory card during recording. The memory card write speed is slow: When recording mov- ies, be sure the memory card write speed is fast enough.
FRAME NO. FULLThe camera has run out of frame numbers (current frame number is 999-9999). Insert a formatted memory card and select RENEW for SAVE DATA SET-UP > FRAME NO.. Take a picture to reset frame numbering to 100-0001, then select CONTINUOUS for FRAME NO..
